snippet: Michael Phelps is again turning this into his Olympics with his 17th overall gold medal in his final individual race, while Missy Franklin set a world record.
abstract: Champion swimmer Michael Phelps wins his 17th Olympic gold medal in his last individual final, the 100-meter butterfly; Missy Franklin, the first woman to compete in seven swimming events at an Olympics, wins her second individual gold and fourth medal of the Games with a world-record-setting performance in her signature 200-meter backstroke; other swimming results noted.
lead_paragraph: Michael Phelps is again turning this into his Olympics with his 17th overall gold medal in his final individual race, while Missy Franklin set a world record.

headline.seo: Phelps and Franklin at Top of Olympic Podium Again
headline.main: Another Pool Day Belongs to Phelps and Franklin
headline.print_headline: Another Pool Day Belongs to Phelps And Franklin
